@chadrik, are you using the `PYTHONPATH` env variable to point to your local development directory?

I'm working on getting `tox` set up on my own project, and I've run into exactly [the import problem you're describing](https://github.com/schematics/schematics/issues/418#issuecomment-219167031).

I haven't nailed down exactly what's going on, but if I have `PYTHONPATH` set to my project's folder, it appears to confuse `pip` and/or `tox` somehow. The upshot is that my package ends up not being installed into the virtualenvs.  Clearing `PYTHONPATH` before calling `tox`, or manually running `pip install --force-reinstall` on each virtualenv, seems to make things play nice. Probably `PYTHONPATH` can be overridden in `tox.ini` somewhere, I just haven't gotten to that point yet.

